trans-unit.source: WorkflowInstance is a lightweight, per-instance runtime for executing a workflow program.
trans-unit.target: WorkflowInstance är en förenklad, per instans runtime för att köra ett arbetsflödesprogram.

trans-unit.source: It can be constructed to create a new workflow instance or from existing instance state.
trans-unit.target: Det kan konstrueras för att skapa en ny arbetsflödesinstans eller från den befintliga instanstillstånd.

trans-unit.source: The APIs that <xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstance.WorkflowInstanceControl> exposes are the minimal set of runtime controls from which higher level operations can be implemented.
trans-unit.target: API: erna som <xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstance.WorkflowInstanceControl>visar är den minsta uppsättningen av runtime-kontroller som högre nivå åtgärder kan genomföras.</xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstance.WorkflowInstanceControl>

trans-unit.source: This API set represents the entire breadth of functionality of the runtime.
trans-unit.target: Den här API-uppsättningen representerar hela bredden av funktionerna i körningsmiljön.

trans-unit.source: WorkflowInstance is an abstract class and relies on a host’s implementation of its abstract methods in order to provide host functionality such as synchronization, persistence, tracking, and extensions.
trans-unit.target: WorkflowInstance är en abstrakt klass och bygger på en värd implementering av de abstrakta metoderna för att kunna tillhandahålla värdfunktioner såsom synkronisering, beständighet, spårning och tillägg.

trans-unit.source: WorkflowInstance is single threaded and assumes that the host synchronizes all access to it.
trans-unit.target: WorkflowInstance är en enskild flertrådade och förutsätter att värden synkroniserar all åtkomst till den.

trans-unit.source: An attempt to call multiple APIs simultaneously will result in an <xref:System.InvalidOperationException> being thrown.
trans-unit.target: Ett försök att anropa flera API: er samtidigt resulterar i en <xref:System.InvalidOperationException>som genereras.</xref:System.InvalidOperationException>

trans-unit.source: Internally, a WorkflowInstance has two states: Running and Paused.
trans-unit.target: Internt, en WorkflowInstance har två lägen: körs och pausad.

trans-unit.source: The only way to cause the runtime to transition from paused to running is to call <xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstance.WorkflowInstanceControl.Run%2A>.
trans-unit.target: Det enda sättet att körningstiden till övergången från pausats körs är att anropa <xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstance.WorkflowInstanceControl.Run%2A>.</xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstance.WorkflowInstanceControl.Run%2A>

trans-unit.source: All actions (except Pause) can only be taken while the runtime is Paused.
trans-unit.target: Alla åtgärder (utom Pause) kan bara hämtas när körningen har pausats.

trans-unit.source: The runtime will become spontaneously Paused in the following situations: - An error fatal to the runtime has occurred.
trans-unit.target: Körningen ska bli spontant pausad i följande situationer:-ett allvarligt körningstillstånd fel har uppstått.

trans-unit.source: The host will be signaled through <xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstance.OnRequestAbort%2A> (which does not signal a transition to Paused) and then notified through <xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstance.OnNotifyPaused%2A>.
trans-unit.target: Värden signaleras via <xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstance.OnRequestAbort%2A>(som ogiltig indikation på en övergång till pausad) och sedan meddelas via <xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstance.OnNotifyPaused%2A>.</xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstance.OnNotifyPaused%2A> </xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstance.OnRequestAbort%2A>

trans-unit.source: - An exception in the workflow was uncaught and escaped the root.
trans-unit.target: -Ett undantag i arbetsflödet var utan felhantering och föregås av roten.

trans-unit.source: The host will be notified through the <xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstance.OnNotifyUnhandledException%2A> method.
trans-unit.target: Värden kommer att meddelas via den <xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstance.OnNotifyUnhandledException%2A>metoden.</xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstance.OnNotifyUnhandledException%2A>

trans-unit.source: - The scheduler has run out of work items and is now <xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstanceState>.
trans-unit.target: -Schemaläggaren har slut arbetsobjekt och är nu <xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstanceState>.</xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstanceState>

trans-unit.source: The host will be notified through the <xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstance.OnNotifyPaused%2A> method.
trans-unit.target: Värden kommer att meddelas via den <xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstance.OnNotifyPaused%2A>metoden.</xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstance.OnNotifyPaused%2A>

trans-unit.source: Note that the scheduler could have run out of work items because the instance is idle or because the instance is complete.
trans-unit.target: Observera att Schemaläggaren kan ha slut arbetsobjekt eftersom instansen är inaktiv eller eftersom instansen är klar.

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstance.WorkflowInstanceControl.State%2A> value of the <xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstance.Controller%2A> property can be used to differentiate between the two.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstance.WorkflowInstanceControl.State%2A>värdet för den <xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstance.Controller%2A>egenskapen kan användas för att skilja mellan två.</xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstance.Controller%2A> </xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstance.WorkflowInstanceControl.State%2A>

trans-unit.source: The host can request a change from Running to Paused by calling the <xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstance.WorkflowInstanceControl.RequestPause%2A> or <xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstance.WorkflowInstanceControl.PauseWhenPersistable%2A> methods of the <xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstance.WorkflowInstanceControl> instance returned by the <xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstance.Controller%2A> property.
trans-unit.target: Värden kan begära en ändring från att köras på Paused genom att anropa den <xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstance.WorkflowInstanceControl.RequestPause%2A>eller <xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstance.WorkflowInstanceControl.PauseWhenPersistable%2A>metoder för den <xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstance.WorkflowInstanceControl>instans som returneras av den <xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstance.Controller%2A>egenskapen.</xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstance.Controller%2A> </xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstance.WorkflowInstanceControl> </xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstance.WorkflowInstanceControl.PauseWhenPersistable%2A> </xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstance.WorkflowInstanceControl.RequestPause%2A>

trans-unit.source: This request should not be considered to have a specific response meaning that the host should not attempt to correlate an OnNotify* or <xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstance.OnRequestAbort%2A> with a specific call to pause. In response to a pause request, the runtime may transition to Paused and call <xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstance.OnNotifyPaused%2A> while the scheduler still has pending work items. The <xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstance.WorkflowInstanceControl.State%2A> value of the <xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstance.Controller%2A> property can be used to determine whether the scheduler has no more work or was interrupted by a request to pause. The <xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstance.WorkflowInstanceControl.RequestPause%2A> method of the <xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstance.WorkflowInstanceControl> instance returned by the <xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstance.Controller%2A> property is the only method which can be called while the WorkflowInstance is in the Running state. All other methods will throw an <xref:System.InvalidOperationException> if called.Given the rules for how WorkflowInstance transitions from one state to another, the public notion of Running and Paused can be defined as follows: - Running – The state between a call to <xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstance.WorkflowInstanceControl.Run%2A> and the next WorkflowInstance.OnNotify*.
trans-unit.target: Denna begäran ska inte betraktas som har ett visst svar vilket innebär att värden inte ska försöka att korrelera ett OnNotify* eller <xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstance.OnRequestAbort%2A>med ett specifikt anrop till pausa.</xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstance.OnRequestAbort%2A> Som svar på en begäran om paus körningen kan övergå till pausas och anropet <xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstance.OnNotifyPaused%2A>medan Schemaläggaren har fortfarande väntande arbetsobjekt.</xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstance.OnNotifyPaused%2A> Den <xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstance.WorkflowInstanceControl.State%2A>värdet för den <xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstance.Controller%2A>egenskapen kan användas för att avgöra om Schemaläggaren har inga fler arbete eller avbröts av en begäran om att pausa.</xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstance.Controller%2A> </xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstance.WorkflowInstanceControl.State%2A> Den <xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstance.WorkflowInstanceControl.RequestPause%2A>metod för den <xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstance.WorkflowInstanceControl>instans som returneras av den <xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstance.Controller%2A>egenskapen är den enda metoden som kan anropas när WorkflowInstance är i tillståndet körs.</xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstance.Controller%2A> </xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstance.WorkflowInstanceControl> </xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstance.WorkflowInstanceControl.RequestPause%2A> Alla andra metoder genereras ett <xref:System.InvalidOperationException>om den anropas. Angivna regler för WorkflowInstance övergången från ett tillstånd till en annan offentlig begreppet körs och pausad kan definieras enligt följande: - kör – tillstånd mellan ett anrop till <xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstance.WorkflowInstanceControl.Run%2A>och nästa WorkflowInstance.OnNotify*.</xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstance.WorkflowInstanceControl.Run%2A> </xref:System.InvalidOperationException>

trans-unit.source: - Paused – The state between the last WorkflowInstance.OnNotify* and the next call to <xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstance.WorkflowInstanceControl.Run%2A>.
trans-unit.target: -Pausad – tillstånd mellan den sista WorkflowInstance.OnNotify* och nästa anrop till <xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstance.WorkflowInstanceControl.Run%2A>.</xref:System.Activities.Hosting.WorkflowInstance.WorkflowInstanceControl.Run%2A>

trans-unit.source: Called by the host to register the specified extension manager, validate that all required extensions are present, and to initialize the collection of extensions to be used.

trans-unit.source: Extensions are keyed by type, and a host provided extension will always be used if provided.
